{"id": 6887, "title": "Ticket #6887: configurable number of retries for credmon polling, part two", "description": "<blockquote>\nIn ticket <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=6169\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6169'); return false;\" title=\"make the number of retries for the credmon polling configurable\">#6169</a></span>, a knob <code>CREDD_POLLING_TIMEOUT</code> was added to control how patient HTCondor should be when waiting for the <code>CREDMON</code> to produce a credential file.\n\n<p>Unfortunately, <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=6169\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6169'); return false;\" title=\"make the number of retries for the credmon polling configurable\">#6169</a></span> did not patch all the places in the code where we are waiting for the <code>CREDMON</code> to do its thing... some places were left hard-coded at 20 seconds.  For instance, when the condor_schedd first starts, and also when the condor_starter potentially signals the <code>CREDMON</code> before launching a job.\n\n</p><p>DESY reported this issue, as they know it can take longer than 20 seconds at times for their CREDMON to create a credential, and they observed starter log errors like the following:\n\n</p><p></p><pre>   StarterLog.slot1_9:01/25/19 12:33:21 (pid:85218) CREDMON: FAILURE: credmon never created /var/lib/condor/credential/xxxxx.cc after 20 seconds!</pre>\n</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2019-Feb-06 16:56:46 by tim:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>CODE REVIEW</strong>: Looks good</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2019-Feb-14 15:03</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valig